    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for giflib.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 10.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "giflib is a library for reading and writing gif images.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* giflib: Giflib: Double-free vulnerability leading to memory corruption (CVE-2026-23868)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
    ],
